        Official Singles Chart on 7/4/2017

        7 April 2017 - 13 April 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Piran

        7th April 2017
        5
        Vote score

        Here are my thoughts on the UK charts this week:

        - THE NUMBER 1: 'Shape Of You' by Ed Sheeran tops the Official Charts for a 13th consecutive week. I still like the song, but it's a shame that it blocked better singles from Ed's album like 'Galway Girl' & 'Castle On The Hill' from reaching #1. That said, I'm very sure that this will be 'Shape Of You's last week at #1; Harry Styles released his debut solo single called 'Sign Of The Times' this morning, which is looking likely to debut at #1 next Friday. At first listen, I would give it a strong 6/10; I prefer Harry's more powerful vocals to his falsetto, but my favourite part of the riff at the end; it reminds me of something David Bowie would've done.

        - THE TOP 10: I'm happy to see 'Stay' & 'Issues' reach the Top 10 today, as both songs grew on me a lot over these past few weeks. It's good that Julia Michaels & Alessia Cara are getting more recognition here now! The former is already a very successful song-writer & the latter is a really talented singer in my opinion. Elsewhere, there wasn't much movement at all, but I like that 'Symphony' is still climbing.

        - 11-40: Of the five new arrivals in this region, my favourite is 'No More Sad Songs', however I prefer the original to the remix; not a huge fan of MGK's verse unfortunately. 'Humble' would be my next favourite (Kendrick's got a decent flow), then 'Swalla' (catchy beat & hilarious lyrics), then 'Mask Off' (don't like the auto-tune, but the flute line is cool). The only debut I didn't like at all this week was 'Heatstroke'; Calvin's production doesn't impress me here, Young Thug sounds boring & Pharrell's upper range is here is a bit annoying to be honest. Ariana's part isn't bad, but she sounds so much better on her own songs. I just prefer the EDM Calvin Harris made back around 2011-12 a lot more.

        - NEXT WEEK'S PREDICTIONS: As mentioned earlier, I think 'Sign Of The Times' will debut at #1 next week & stay at #1 for at least a month. Even though it has no chance of #1 now, I can also see 'Galway Girl' passing 'Shape Of You' within the next week or two. 'No More Sad Songs' will probably go Top 10 & we could also see also see 'Places' & 'Die With You' enter the Top 40 next Friday.

        Thanks for reading everyone & have a nice weekend! :)

        "Mr. Brightside" by the Killers is four weeks away from setting a new record for the most weeks in the Top 100 of the Official UK Singles Chart. It's now been in the Top 100 for a combined period of 163 weeks. The current record for the most weeks in the Top 100 is held by "Chasing Cars" by Snow Patrol, which was on the charts for a combined period of 166 weeks. The record I'm referring to is for combined weeks, so if a song temporarily left the charts and then re-entered it would still be in contention. The record for the longest continuous run in the Top 100 (without leaving the charts) is 95 weeks for "Thinking Out Loud" by Ed Sheeran.

        Ed Sheeran continues to dominate the Official UK Singles Chart this week. He holds the Top 2 spots, with "Shape Of You" (at number 1) and "Galway Girl" (at number 2). "Shape Of You" has now held the top spot for 13 weeks.

        "Symphony" by Clean Bandit featuring (19 year old Swedish singer/songwriter) Zara Larsson rises one place to number 3 this week. This song has already reached number 1 in Sweden, becoming the fifth number one from Larsson in her native land.

        "Passionfruit" by Drake falls one place to number 4 this week. It's the second single from Drake's new playlist entitled "More Life". It's a dancehall pop song written by Drake along with British producer-songwriter Nana Rogues and has additional vocals from Zoe Kravitz (Zoe Kravitz is the daughter of musician Lenny Kravitz and actress Lisa Bonet). "Passionfruit" is performed in the key of G# minor in common time with a tempo of 112 beats per minute. Drake's vocals span from F#3 to G#4.

        "Something Just Like This" by the Chainsmokers and Coldplay rounds off the Top 5 this week. It's the second single off the Chainsmokers' debut studio album, "Memories...Do Not Open" which dropped today (April 7, 2017) via Disruptor Records and Columbia Records.

        "Humble" by Kendrick Lamar debuts at number 21. It was produced by Mike Will Made It and Pluss. The song's accompanying music video (directed by Dave Meyers and The Little Homies) was released on March 30, 2017 on Kendrick's Vevo account.

        "Sign Of the Times" by Harry Styles was released today. I'm expecting it to debut on the chart next week (hopefully in the Top 10). I think it's the best of all the songs released by One Direction members (that's just my opinion).
